  m_text: "Dear Diary,\r\nToday was a very interesting day at the Academy.\r\nAfter
    classes, I went to the library and read several old books about the Golden Speaking
    Ball. The more I read, the more fascinated I became. Every book said something
    different, but they all agreed on one thing: the Ball opened hidden doors and
    revealed secrets.\r\nLater, I went to the display hall and saw the Golden Speaking
    Ball with my own eyes. It looked even more impressive than I remembered. I stood
    there for several minutes and thought about all the possibilities it offered.\r\nDuring
    lunch, I saw Whinnyham again. He laughed at my clothes and said they looked old-fashioned.
    He didn't understand my style at all. I didn't say much, but I felt angry. One
    day, I thought, I would show him.\r\nAfter school, my band met in the secret
    cellar room underneath the library. We went there through the hidden passage
    behind the bookshelves. While we practised, I told them about the Golden Speaking
    Ball. They listened politely, but they didn't seem as interested as I was.\nLater
    that evening, I wrote down some ideas.\r\nIf I became a teacher at the Academy
    one day, I could enter rooms that students couldn't enter. Teachers knew the
    schedules, the keys and many secrets of the Academy. I suddenly thought of something
    strange. What if somebody took the Golden Speaking Ball? Would anyone suspect
    a teacher? Probably not. That is a very interesting idea. \r\n\u2014 Fiona"
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
